---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About FidoHikes" description="The story behind FidoHikes — built by Toby & Trisha, AT thru-hikers who know what it takes to adventure with dogs.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-800 text-earth mb-6">About FidoHikes</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        FidoHikes was born on the Appalachian Trail. When we thru-hiked the AT, we learned firsthand
        what gear works, what doesn't, and what keeps your dog safe mile after mile.
      </p>
      <p>
        Now we share what we've learned — honest gear reviews, trail-tested safety advice,
        and destination guides for every dog owner who wants to explore the outdoors with their best friend.
      </p>
      <h2>What We Cover</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Gear Reviews</strong> — We test harnesses, boots, packs, and accessories on real trails</li>
        <li><strong>Trail Guides</strong> — Dog-friendly destinations across the US</li>
        <li><strong>Safety</strong> — First aid, weather prep, and hazard awareness</li>
        <li><strong>Training</strong> — Trail manners, off-leash skills, and socialization</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Our Review Process</h2>
      <p>
        Every product we recommend has been used on trails. We buy most gear ourselves and test it
        in real conditions. Our reviews include honest pros and cons — we're not here to sell you
        something that won't hold up on mile 10.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
